    "description": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across three grid levels (coarse 2.1M cells, medium 5.8M cells, fine 14.2M cells) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. Grid convergence index (GCI) computed for wall shear stress and velocity magnitude at five operating points spanning the CPB flow-speed matrix. Richardson extrapolation applied to quantify discretization error bounds. Study confirms mesh-independent solution at medium grid level with GCI < 3% for all quantities of interest.",
